    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-07T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/495: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-07T21:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 7, 1936—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 7—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1078. The Third Committee this afternoon approved a report<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d12fn22">League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official Journal</hi>,
                        Special Supplement No. 158, Annex, p. 26.</note> to the Assembly which
                    summarized its deliberations and states that “while the Committee expresses the
                    hope that there will be an early meeting of the Bureau, it nevertheless realizes
                    that the date of convocation and the result of its discussions depend very
                    largely on the important negotiations which are so frequently mentioned at
                    present.”</p>
                <p>A resolution was also prepared for the Assembly’s approval welcoming the
                    initiative taken by the French with a view to the early convocation of the
                        Bureau.<note n="23" xml:id="d12fn23">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, No. 153, p. 19.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
